      • compare

        public static int compare(Object x,
                          Object y)
        Compares two object for ordering.

        Comparison is consistent with Google Datastore sorting rules, with the following deterministic ordering for mixed value types:

        • null values;
        • integral values;
        • date values;
        • boolean values;
        • string values;
        • floating-point values;
        • datastore key values;
        • property container values (label/id/key order);
        • other values (system-dependent order).
        Parameters:
        x - the first object to be compared.
        y - the second object to be compared.
        Returns:
        a negative integer, zero, or a positive integer as the x is less than, equal to, or greater than y
